<div id="nodeDecoration"><div id="headerContent"><h1 id="nodeTitle">3.2 Reporting verbs</h1></div></div>
<div class="iDevice_wrapper FreeTextIdevice" id="id208">
<div class="iDevice emphasis0">
<div id="ta208_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<p>There are many verbs which can be used to introduce reported speech. Each one is followed by different grammatical patterns. Most verbs can be followed by more than one pattern.</p>
<p><b>Verb + Infinitive</b></p>
<p>agree<br />decide<br />offer<br />promise<br />refuse<br />threaten</p>
<p><i>Ex: She offered to give him a lift</i></p>
<p><b>Verb + Object + Infinitive</b></p>
<p>advise<br />encourage<br />invite<br />remind<br />warn</p>
<p><i>EX: My parents encouraged me to travel.</i></p>
<p><b>Verb + object + Preposition + Gerund</b></p>
<p>accuse<br />blame<br />congratulate</p>
<p><i>Ex: The woman accused him of stealing her purse.</i></p>
<p><b>Verb + (that) + Sentence</b></p>
<p>admit<br />agree<br />decide<br />deny<br />explain<br />insist<br />promise<br />recommend<br />suggest</p>
<p>Ex: T<i>om admitted (that) he had cheated in the exam</i></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
